modules.description: Detects MIME types from file content using magic number signatures, supports byte sequences and file paths, and enables proper handling of binary data in network protocols. Processes raw data buffers and file descriptors to identify file formats accurately. Used to determine content types for HTTP responses and to route data to appropriate parsers or viewers.

Generates and executes a decision tree to determine a file's MIME type and metadata from a directory or string input. Processes files using a tree structure built from a database or serialized data, returning optional output and MIME type information. Supports merging trees and handling errors through a result type.
